</li>
<li id="cite_note-47"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-47">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Incidentally, before gas lighting was introduced in 1875, the breaks between acts in operas had to be timed to allow the replacement of candles in chandeliers. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=6657712">"The Interplay of Opera, Candles and the Court"</a> by Susan Stamberg, 21 December 2006, <i>Morning Edition</i>, <a href="/wiki/NPR" title="NPR">NPR</a></span>
